# Risk

Project context can diverge across OKF, backlog tasks, adapters, MCP state, generated packs, and chat history. OKF can also become unsafe if secrets or credentials are committed.

# Impact

- Agents may implement stale requirements.
- Durable decisions may be missed during review.
- Credentials may leak through Git history.

# Likelihood

Medium unless validation and update habits are followed.

# Mitigations

- Keep adapters thin.
- Run `scripts/okf-validate`.
- Use `okf_concepts` for traceability.
- Store secrets only in approved secret stores.

# Monitoring

- Review `.okf/log.md`.
- Check `.okf/improvements/` at milestones.
- Run launch validation before release gates.
